               <msContents class="thematic">
                  <summary>This manuscript contains a translation of the book of Aphorisms attributed to <persName type="standard" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/287984736" key="person_287984736">Hippocrates</persName>.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_119_tibb_taymur-item1">
                     <author key="person_19690624">
                        <persName ref="viaf.org/viaf/19690624" type="aut">Ḥunayn ibn Isḥāq‏حنين بن إسحق</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="desc" key="work_7773">Arabic Translation of the Hippocratic Aphorisms</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="work_7773">Fuṣūl Abuqrāṭ</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_7773">فصول أبقراط</title>
                     <note>Original manuscript in Egyptian National Library.</note>
                     <note>This is a collection of the Hippocratic lemmata of <persName type="standard" key="person_19690624" ref="viaf.org/viaf/19690624">Ḥunayn</persName>'s version thematically arranged based on <persName type="standard" key="person_4405945" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/4405945">Ibn Abī Ṣādiq</persName>'s thematic commentary. The introduction begins on <locus>p. 2</locus>. The beginning of each chapter is as follows: ch. 1: 2; ch. 2: 3; ch. 3: 5; ch. 4: 8; ch. 5: 9; ch. 6: 12; ch. 7: 20; (ch. 8 is missing); ch. 9: 24; (ch. 10 is missing); ch. 11: 26; ch. 12: 26; ch. 13: 144a; ch. 14: 27; ch. 15: 29; ch. 16: 31; (chs. 17-20 are missing).</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
